OL,3,CKiller of Nathan Gibson ordered to
OL,4,Cspend more time behind bars
OL,6,FLady Chief Justice Dame Siobhan Keegan
OL,7,Fheld: "The sentence was unduly lenient
OL,8,Fgiven the element of pre-planning and
OL,9,Fthe fact that a brutal multiple
OL,10,Fstabbing such as this required an
OL,11,Fuplift to reflect the horrific nature
OL,12,Fof this crime."
OL,14,FWhitla must now serve at least 19
OL,15,Fyears behind bars before he can apply
OL,16,Fto be released on licence.
OL,18,FThe murder was carried out during a
OL,19,Fsuspected drug-related encounter
OL,20,Fbetween the two men on a towpath near
OL,21,FLake Road.
