OL,3,CKiller of Nathan Gibson ordered to
OL,4,Cspend more time behind bars
OL,6,FPost-mortem examinations revealed 25-
OL,7,Fyear-old Mr Gibson had been stabbed 18
OL,8,Ftimes to the head and a further 31
OL,9,Ftimes in the neck.
OL,11,FOne of the knife wounds went through
OL,12,Fhis eye socket into the brain, while
OL,13,Fanother left the tip of the blade
OL,14,Fembedded in his skull.
OL,16,FWhitla left the scene covered in blood
OL,17,Fand went to Mr Gibson's home where he
OL,18,Fmanaged to convince the victim's
OL,19,Fpartner to help clean him up.
