OL,3,CKiller of Nathan Gibson ordered to
OL,4,Cspend more time behind bars
OL,6,FHe threatened and held the woman
OL,7,Fcaptive, at one point suggesting he
OL,8,Fhad been told to carry out the murder
OL,9,Fby a local drugs gang known as 'The
OL,10,FFirm'.
OL,12,FWhitla, of no fixed abode and known by
OL,13,Fthe nickname 'Eyeball Paul', pleaded
OL,14,Fguilty to murdering Mr Gibson as well
OL,15,Fas common assault and false
OL,16,Fimprisonment of his girlfriend.
OL,18,FIn December 2023, he was sentenced to
OL,19,Flife imprisonment, with a minimum
OL,20,Ftariff of 15 years before he can be
OL,21,Fconsidered for release.
