OL,3,CKiller of Nathan Gibson ordered to
OL,4,Cspend more time behind bars
OL,6,FThe Public Prosecution Service (PPS)
OL,7,Fappealed the term imposed by arguing
OL,8,Fthat the degree of premeditation in
OL,9,Fthe killing justified a higher tariff.
OL,11,FDefence lawyers responded that Whitla
OL,12,Fwas impaired by a low IQ and claimed
OL,13,Fthe challenge was devoid of merit.
OL,15,FIn her ruling, the Lady Chief Justice
OL,16,Fsaid the sentencing judge had been led
OL,17,Finto error because the prosecution
OL,18,Funderestimated the extent of pre-
OL,19,Fplanning to the killing.
