OL,3,CKiller of Nathan Gibson ordered to
OL,4,Cspend more time behind bars
OL,6,F"In our view the respondent's actions
OL,7,Fin arming himself with a knife and
OL,8,Finflicting multiple stab wounds cannot
OL,9,Fsimply be explained as a drug
OL,10,Frendezvous gone wrong," she said.
OL,12,FCiting the brutality involved in
OL,13,Frepeatedly stabbing a vulnerable
OL,14,Fvictim in the face and neck, Dame
OL,15,FSiobhan held: "These stark facts mean
OL,16,Fthat the judge was entitled to
OL,17,Fincrease the starting point by varying
OL,18,Fthe sentence upwards from a minimum
OL,19,Ftariff when high culpability was
OL,20,Festablished."
